## STANDARD SCREENS (Clean and functional)

These screens use established patterns. They should be well-designed but don't need to be the hero moments.

### Screen 4: Bookings

Segmented tabs: Upcoming, Active, Past

**Booking cards include:**
- Provider name + avatar
- Service type
- Date/time
- Status badge
- Quick actions (message, reschedule)

**Active bookings — richer status tracking:**
Status progression: Confirmed → Provider en route → Arriving in X min → In progress → Completed

Styled similarly to Uber/Instacart order tracking — visual timeline, live status.

**Empty states:**
- Upcoming: "No upcoming bookings. Need something fixed?" + CTA to search
- Active: "Nothing in progress right now."
- Past: "Your completed services will show up here."

### Screen 5: Booking Detail / Status Tracker

Full detail view for an active booking.

Includes:
- Booking summary (service, date, time, address)
- Provider info (name, photo, rating)
- ETA (when applicable)
- Visual status timeline: Request submitted → Provider confirmed → On the way → In progress → Completed
- Service notes
- Contact / message provider CTA
- Reschedule / cancel CTA
- Price summary

### Screen 6: Messages

**List view:**
- Provider conversations listed by recency
- Each row: provider avatar, name, last message preview, timestamp, unread indicator

**Conversation detail:**
Three message types, visually distinct:
- User messages — standard chat bubbles
- Provider messages — standard chat bubbles, different alignment/color
- System/agent messages — muted inline style (like a timestamp divider with text, NOT a chat bubble). Examples: "Your booking has been confirmed.", "Provider updated ETA to 10:42 AM."

**Empty state:** "No conversations yet. Messages with providers will appear here."

### Screen 7: Profile

Sections:
- Personal info (name, email, phone)
- Saved addresses
- Payment methods (display only, no payment processing)
- Service preferences
- Support
- Become a service provider (CTA link, no destination needed)

